result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeanne M Eanes was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jeanne M Eanes is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jeanne M Eanes was found guilty of Possession of Controlled Substance, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).

Defendant Jeanne M Eanes in court with attorney Henry Francis Mcroberts.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 10:41 PM. State - here for change of plea and sentencing, Count 1 - G/NC plea to amended 961.41(3g)(b) - other drugs, $500 fine plus costs. Count 2 would be dismissed, DE would be asking for payment plan. Court dismisses count 2. Court amends charge to 961.41(3g)(b), reads new penalties. Defendant pleads NC to amended charge. Court goes over PLQ, finds the defendant is freely, voluntairly and intelligently entering her plea, waiving her constitutial rights and right to JT. Court finds factual basis and adjudges guilty. State makes final statement and asks court to follow joint recommendation. Mcroberts makes final statement and asks to follow joint recommendation. Eanes makes statement, remorseful. Court accepts joint recommendation and sentences to the following: Count 1 - imposes fine of $500 plus costs, apply bond posted, $50/month commencing 6/15/16. DNA sample required - expunction of DNA rights given, appeal rights given.
